@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@
+# Corridor: list-json-flag
+
+Add a `--json` flag to the `list` command so it prints notes as a JSON array.
+
+## Start Frontier
+- `cli_notes/cli.py::cmd_list` — currently loops `store.load(args.store)` printing `id\ttext`.
+- `cli_notes/cli.py::build_parser` — the `list` subparser.
+- `cli_notes/store.py::load` — returns the list of note dicts (read-only, unchanged).
+
+## Goal Frontier
+- `list --json` prints a valid JSON array of the notes.
+- Without `--json`, output is unchanged (`id\ttext` lines).
+- Empty store with `--json` prints `[]`.
+
+## Paths
+- cli_notes/cli.py
+- tests/test_cli.py
